OL,3,CWho is Darragh Mackin? The solicitor
OL,4,Cbacking the Summerland campaign
OL,6,F"The reality is both have been riddled
OL,7,Fwith failed investigations, in my
OL,8,Fview, and secondly, both have at their
OL,9,Fepicentre a previous finding that
OL,10,Findeed almost puts blame on the very
OL,11,Fvictims who went there.
OL,13,F"The verdict in the Summerland of
OL,14,F'misadventure' attaches with it the
OL,15,Fabsence of any blame or
OL,16,Fresponsibility, and indeed the absence
OL,17,Fof any culpability for any other
OL,18,Fperson.
